column3: Zamek Ogrodzieniec is the ruins of a castle situated in the Kraków-Częstochowa Upland, built in the system known as the Eagle Nests, in the village of Podzamcze in the Silesian Voivodeship, in the Zawiercie County, approximately 2 km east of Ogrodzieniec. The castle was constructed in the 14th - 15th centuries by the Włodków Sulimczyków family.

The village is located in the Małopolskie Voivodeship, in the Krakowski County, within the Skała municipality, in the Kraków-Częstochowa Upland, in the Prądnik Valley, along the Eagles' Nests Trail. During the Kingdom of Poland, there was a commune named Ojców. From 1975 to 1998, the village was situated in the Kraków Voivodeship. From 1928 to 1966, Ojców held the status of a health resort with public utility character.
